{"title":"Setup","markdown":{"yaml":{"title":"Setup"},"headingText":"What you need","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\nBefore starting the lessons, make sure the computer has the tools needed to run Python.\n\n\nYou need:\n\n- **Python**: the programming language.\n- **Positron**: the coding environment where you write and run Python programs.\n- **Quarto**: only needed if you want to render this course website yourself.\n\n## Folder structure\n\nCreate a folder for your course work, for example:\n\n```text\nPythonCourseWork/\n├── lesson1.py\n├── lesson2.py\n├── games/\n└── experiments/\n```\n\nPut your Python files in this folder.\n\n## Check that Python works\n\nOpen a terminal in Positron and type:\n\n```bash\npython --version\n```\n\nYou should see a Python version number.\n\nThen create a file called:\n\n```text\nhello.py\n```\n\nwith this code:\n\n```python\nprint(\"Hello, Python!\")\n```\n\nRun it from the terminal:\n\n```bash\npython hello.py\n```\n\nIf you see:\n\n```text\nHello, Python!\n```\n\nthen Python is working.\n\n::: {.callout-note}\n## On some Windows computers\n\nYou may need to type `py hello.py` instead of `python hello.py`.\n:::\n\n## How to use this course locally\n\nTo build the full website, open this folder in Positron and run:\n\n```bash\nquarto render\n```\n\nThe finished website will appear in:\n\n```text\n_book/\n```\n\nOpen:\n\n```text\n_book/index.html\n```\n\nin your browser.\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":"\n\nBefore starting the lessons, make sure the computer has the tools needed to run Python.\n\n## What you need\n\nYou need:\n\n- **Python**: the programming language.\n- **Positron**: the coding environment where you write and run Python programs.\n- **Quarto**: only needed if you want to render this course website yourself.\n\n## Folder structure\n\nCreate a folder for your course work, for example:\n\n```text\nPythonCourseWork/\n├── lesson1.py\n├── lesson2.py\n├── games/\n└── experiments/\n```\n\nPut your Python files in this folder.\n\n## Check that Python works\n\nOpen a terminal in Positron and type:\n\n```bash\npython --version\n```\n\nYou should see a Python version number.\n\nThen create a file called:\n\n```text\nhello.py\n```\n\nwith this code:\n\n```python\nprint(\"Hello, Python!\")\n```\n\nRun it from the terminal:\n\n```bash\npython hello.py\n```\n\nIf you see:\n\n```text\nHello, Python!\n```\n\nthen Python is working.\n\n::: {.callout-note}\n## On some Windows computers\n\nYou may need to type `py hello.py` instead of `python hello.py`.\n:::\n\n## How to use this course locally\n\nTo build the full website, open this folder in Positron and run:\n\n```bash\nquarto render\n```\n\nThe finished website will appear in:\n\n```text\n_book/\n```\n\nOpen:\n\n```text\n_book/index.html\n```\n\nin your browser.\n"},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":false,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":false,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"message":false,"engine":"markdown"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":"none","code-overflow":"wrap","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":false,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":1,"latex-max-runs":10,"latex-makeindex":"makeindex","latex-makeindex-opts":[],"latex-tlmgr-opts":[],"latex-input-paths":[],"latex-output-dir":null,"link-external-icon":false,"link-external-new